can you explain what you are trying to do? its a Metro Problem? You dont want to enter Metro settings at all after booting into an Image created from a fresh install that was set to skip Metro settings?<br /><br />Could it be that you need to go through the process of creating some default settings then create a new Image?<br /><br />I've never used this, but may be worth a try before you make your Image: <a href="http://www.thewindowsclub.com/metro-ui-tweaker-windows-8-released" class="postlink">Metro UI Tweaker</a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=359">Tenzen</a> — Wed Mar 20, 2013 10:06 pm</p><hr />
